Jerri Chen

Me at Work

I’m a pediatric anesthesiologist at New York Presbyterian Morgan Stanley Children’s Hospital and Assistant Professor of Anesthesiology at Columbia University Irving Medical Center in New York City.

I received my MD and PhD degrees from the Medical Scientist Training Program at the Albert Einstein College of Medicine, and a BA from Wellesley College. A native New Yorker, I attended Hunter College High School.

Me Not at Work

Outside of work I dabble in choral singing with The Cecilia Chorus of New York and in running. I ran my first marathon in 2018.
